    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Early Spanish rugs characterized by a woolen pile tied with Spanish knots to an undyed woolen foundation, generally somber in color, often with a red ground and geometrical design motifs reminiscent of Classic Anatolian rugs.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
